# Lakebase project – common ignores
.env
application-local.properties
.tmp/
*.log
.DS_Store

# TDD per-run observability (NOT planning corpus): the agent event log + the
# resolved run-config snapshot are local to a single run/feature drive and are
# re-initialized each run, so they must never enter git history (a stray
# `git add -A` from a build commit would otherwise carry one feature's log onto
# the next branch). The committed .sftdd corpus (features/, planning/, sprints/,
# workflow-state.json, product-overview.md, nfrs.md, design/) is unaffected.
.sftdd/agent-log.jsonl
.sftdd/run-config.json

# The kit-ref RUN PIN: a WORKSPACE-local, checkout-proof override of the committed
# `.lakebase/kit-ref`. The drive writes it at launch to pin the run's kit version
# for the whole run; it MUST stay gitignored so a branch checkout/reset (which
# forks from origin/<parent>) can never restore a branch-committed kit-ref out from
# under the run and silently execute the wrong kit version. The committed
# `.lakebase/kit-ref` stays tracked (CI resolves its KIT_REF from it).
.lakebase/kit-ref.local

# Per-agent local memory: each role subagent (memory: project) persists its own
# learnings here mid-run. It is local + churny (re-written every run), not feature
# code, so it must never be committed nor count as a dirty working tree , an
# untracked .claude/agent-memory/ otherwise blocks the experiment-branch fork
# (assertCleanForFork) the moment a role saves a memory.
.claude/agent-memory/
